track_notes: This cuts across a meadow to the PCT and a use trail through steep gully to Mason Valley Truck Trail. Summit is reached via rocky path along a firebreak.
track_title: Chariot Mtn. from Fages Monument Trailhead

track_notes:
Started at the California Riding & Hiking Trail N of Sunrise Hwy and cut across the meadow to a short section of the PCT, then on to a faint use trail. Finally took two rights on the network of truck trails to follow an old firebreak up to the summit.

The most difficult section was between the truck trails and the PCT on the way back to the trail head, since it was uphill and I may have lost the `trail` a couple of times in thick vegetation.

Disclaimer: I have not ridden this route. Attempt at your own risk and happy adventuring. Although tempting (PCT = Perfect Cycling Trail), mountain biking not permitted on the Pacific Crest Trail. This route crosses the PCT once.
